Local peritoneal factors: their role in infertility associated with endometriosis. In order to detect peritoneal abnormalities that could account for infertility associated with endometriosis, 122 infertile individuals were studied at the time of laparoscopy for diagnostic purposes or for in vitro fertilization. Four groups were defined: group 1, laparoscopy without endometriosis group 2, laparoscopy with endometriosis